KCCAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

KCCAns:
Irrigation and drainage:

Irrigation should be done immediately after harvesting of Kharif season crop, otherwise the possibility of delaying the plant will delay the irrigation. When the monsoon is harvested on the onion crop grown in Kharif season, irrigation should be done as per the requirement. It should be noted that there should be no shortage of water at the time of construction of Shalkankanda, because it is a revolutionary state of the onion crop, because in this stage there is a shortage of yield due to lack of water, while the excess amount of water purple smear (Pillar Batch) invites disease. The farm should not be dry for a long time, otherwise the Shalankand will burst and the crop will come soon, resulting in less production. Therefore, light irrigation should be done from 8-10 days intervals as required. If the water in the field stops due to excess rainfall or other reason then it should be arranged to remove it quickly, otherwise the chances of fungal growth are increased in the crop.

KCCAns:
earthworm farmers and the intestines of land are called. These concentrated substances spread humus and soil and spread them to other layers inside the ground. With this the ground is polar and the air traffic increases and the increase in storage capacity is increased. The action of chemical action and microbes in the stomach of earthworms increases the availability of nitrogen, phosphor and potash and other subtle elements found in the soil. Vermi compost does not contain stench and flies and mosquitoes do not grow and the atmosphere is not polluted. By controlling the temperature, the bacteria are active and active. Vermi compost gets ready within one and a half months. It contains 2.5 to 3% nitrogen, 1.5 to 2% phosphor and 1.5 to 2% potash.

Preparation Method:

The fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, fertilize 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sail for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top so that the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted doubles, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform so that the worm wash can be collected.

KCCAns:
1- Visit the field in which the sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with the hands and put on clean clothes and make a round pile. Remove the clay from the finger to the four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure till almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. An information sheet along with the sample on which all the information is written, put it in a plastic bag and outside the clothes bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns: Sagotrin aloe           -   Aloe perryi ,ALOE INFLORESCENCE--Aloe vera,These are the three mainly cultivated types of aloe. Certain other types like Zanzibar, Uganda, Natal and Hyderabad aloe are having good quality of “aloe gel”. Soil and Climate--Well drained laterite to loamy soils is suited for aloe cultivation. The soil pH must be ranged from 7.0 to 8.5. Commercial cultivation can be done in regions having 25 – 40°C.Seed and sowing---It is propagated through suckers. The suckers are dipped in 0.1 % Carbendazim for five minutes and planted in the field. For planting one hectare of land, 10,000 suckers are required.Planting season---The planting can be done during two seasons namely June – July and September – October.Planting---Field is thoroughly ploughed and beds of suitable sizes are formed. Suckers are planted at 90 x 90 cm spacing.
